			<div id="smp-title" class="max mdl-grid">
				<div class="mdl-cell mdl-cell--3-col">
				</div>
				<div class="mdl-cell mdl-cell--9-col">
					<h3 style="color:gray">Packaging Samples</h3>
				</div>
			</div>
				
			
			<div class="max mdl-grid">
				<div class="mdl-cell mdl-cell--3-col">
					<!--center><img src="/packages/sarai_sarai-pests/public/images/clinic/plant_black.png" width="200px;" height="200px;" style="padding-top:20px"/></center-->
				</div>
				<div class="mdl-cell mdl-cell--9-col">
					<h4 class="smp-text"><b>Plant Samples</b></h4>
					<ol>
						<li>Carefully examine the plant.</li>
						<li>Ideally, sending the whole plant is the best option.
							Place the root ball in a plastic bag and wrap the leaves with paper. Send the sample as soon as possible.
						</li>
						<li>If the plant is large: 
							<ul>
								<li>Cover the leaves with dry paper and put it into a ziplock plastic bag.</li>
								<li>Do the same on cut stems.</li>
								<li>Shake of the soil from the roots. Wrap it with a barely damp towel and put it in a plastic bag.</li>
							</ul>
						</li>
					</ol>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="max mdl-grid">
				<div class="mdl-cell mdl-cell--3-col">
					<!--center><img src="/packages/sarai_sarai-pests/public/images/clinic/insect_black.png" width="200px;" height="200px;" style="padding-top:20px"/></center-->
				</div>
				<div class="mdl-cell mdl-cell--9-col">
					<h4 class="smp-text"><b>Insect Samples</b></h4>
					<ol>
						<li>All insects should be placed in a small leak-proff container.</li>
						<li>Tiny and/or soft-bodied specimen should be submitted in a container with 70 percent alcohol.</li>
						<li>Hard-bodied specimens can be submitted dry on a crush-proof environment.</li>
					</ol>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			
				<div class="max mdl-grid">
					<div class="mdl-cell mdl-cell--3-col">
					</div>
					<div class="mdl-cell mdl-cell--9-col">
						<div class="smp-note bg">
							<h5>Note:</h5>
							<p>Samples should be sent after packaging. If this cannot be done on the same day, refrigerate the sample.</p>
							<p>Ideally, samples should be hand-carried to the lab. If sending through mail, send the sample early in week to avoid the package arrival on weekends.</p>
					</div>
					<br/>
				</div>
			
			</div>
	</div>

	
